tips.text: The ippudo karaka was awesome. I tried with the level 3 spicy and it boasted great flavour. Adding garlic to it was a great final touch. Highly recommended for those that like spicy flavourful ramen.
Always 1 of our favorite ramen; Ippudo.  The Roppongi branch is spacious and staffs are courtesy and efficient. Obviously the ramen is superb!! üòç a must if u r in Japan!
A dozen combo in 3 types of soup base. We went 4d Karaka Chashu & Shiromaru Special. Both excellent. Noodles r firm. Soup not2 oily. What else we liked? Friendly waiters. Comfy ambience.

Looking for a good spot for ramen amidst all the options in Tokyo?  This place in Roppongi is amazing. The special ramen is great and the Kara is good for those who like their ramen on the spicy side.
Seriously amazing ramen! They officially open at 11, but let people in around 10:30, so come early for breakfast if you don't want to wait in line!
The Ramen is good in this restaurant. The taste was so great! I ordered the red packet, the soup taset was strong and felt perfect with the ramen üëçüèæüëçüèæüëçüèæ
Kara Ramen the spicy one is awesome. Their gyoza is worth trying too. It has a dash of yuzu on the meat that I find enjoyable.
Very good ramen. You can add fresh garlic, which makes it even better. Don‚Äôt take the spicy ramen, though it‚Äôs not as good as the regular one, although decent enough
The of the great ramen chains. Ramen lovers dont want to miss going to japan without visiting Ippudo at least once.
Incredible ramen, get the special, extra firm noodles. The waiters are very friendly and speak good English soo!
Best burgers in Tokyo. Try the Broccoli Cheeseburger. Drizzle the leftover sauce on your fries.
One of the best burgers here in Tokyo! The place is very cosy, the staff are nice, the Double Cheeseburger is my favorite.
Like most Japanese burgers, this one has a thin patty, so get a double if you like a lot of meat. It‚Äôs perfectly seasoned with just salt and pepper. They mix the ketchup and mayo into a sauce.
Cheeseburger is so yummi! Best burger I've ever tried in Tokyoüëåüèªüëåüèª
Go for the broccoli cheeseburger and karakuchi ginger ale. You might need to use the bag - burgers are a bit oily.
Amazing hamburgers. Best I've had in Japan. Try the avocado or broccoli for something different.
Absolutely everything is good here.  Every time I go I'm quite happy.
Original and delicious burgers. Samuel Adams Boston lager available. English menus. You'll probably want to come back, so ask for a point card.
Very good and authentic American burger!
Some fun toys and games for entertainment but no high chairs. Good music. Not crowded at lunch on weekend.

They have a bunch of choices of udons!I personally love their soup udons, and since it's close to roppongi best place for food after clubbing! It's always packed around five but you should def try it!

This place is one of the best places to eat udon. And the best part is, if you can eat 3 servings of udon noodles, you don't have to pay at all. This is per person and cannot be shared. I tried.. üòú
be prepared for a wait ! just put down your name and you can kill time elsewhere around Roppongi, even if they pass you just let them know when you come back and they'll call you up next
Their portion is ginormous and their menu had picture perfect shots for those who don't read japanese
Creamy cod roe udon is amazing. Huge portion of extremely good udon for a reasonable dinner price, ¬•800-¬•1600

Not going to tell you what to get because a lot of stuff seems good here. I got the special curry udon. The broth was thick and tasty and the tempura was well fried & not greasy. More beef than noodle
Most innovative udon menu in Tokyo with large servings ensured to make you full, but 1.5x noodles is plenty
Besides the udon, the tempura dishes are delicious.  Had a Sanma ume tempura dish as well as their tempura mix.  Recommend both.
open til really late and great great comfort food. the sukiyaki beef udon was great
1580 yen for beef sukiyaki udon. Huge bowl. Be prepared to wait during lunch :)
All dishes are pretty good as everybody loves this restaurant.
The chicken casserole noodles and the curry pork are fantastic. Everything else is average.
Pls try Chicken noodle and curry rice. My roppongi classic. Open midnight.
The lady that took our order was very rude. D+ for service. B for food. The egg rolls with shrimp and mushrooms and a chicken soup we had were delicious. The chop suey chow mein was weird tasting.
Delicious chicken soba noodles... something that anyone should try at least once...
Bit expensive. Not really authentic Chinese food, more Japanese-style than Chinese.
Tokusei Tori nikomi soba 1,300JPY

One of the best club lounges I have been to out of any Intercontinental‚Äôs in the world. Service is on point as one would expect in Japan. Food and beverage menu is extensive and the views are amazing!
Great food and great service. Make sure to stop by for breakfast, afternoon tea, and drinks.

This is considered the best maido cafe in Roppongi.  It's 1100 Yen per hour and then 550 for each half hour thereafter.  You should experience it at least once!
Tough to find!  Go to the family mart, head to the 6th floor.  Affilia Stars Diner. You're welcome.

If you like beer this place is a must! The food is also amazing and the staff are extremely friendly. As a foreigner I felt comfortable and welcome. Favorite place to eat/ drink in Tokyo so far!
Bring a date who loves draft beer. Great rotating selection of craft brews in an intimate setting. The bar is also the kitchen. Not necessarily good for large groups but try anyway!

finding a good beer place is just as hard as finding a good ramen place. fortunately ive found the former. this is my goto beer place so far while exploring tokyo. craftheads was closed and in shibuyu
Japan‚Äôs craft-beer scene is having a moment; at this cellar bar, you‚Äôll find a wide variety of local brews on tap. Try the Shiga Kogen Miyama Blonde, made in Nagano.
Good selection of craft beers, open until 6am and we had food at 4am, what more do you need?
Solid craft beer bar with no seating fee & bilingual beer & bar food menu. 20+ domestic craft brews on tap, good range but didn't find anything I hadn't seen before. Drink prices a little high.
A little hard to find: you have to look for the tiny sign and go down the stairs. But great beers and you can taste before you buy. Small space so don't try to bring a group here.
Good selection of regional beers, and a pint costs 1200 Yen (+Tax), sign outside not representative of the beers they sell. Small place downstairs but bright and welcoming, limited English spoken.
Tiny place, crowded, wonderful beer selection. Great visit to enjoy nice local craft beer.
Good japanese draft beer. Cozy atmosphere and nice staff. Food is definitely not japanese. Free wifi.
very tasty mapo tofu, lots of spices.

If you are a BrewDog fan, you naturally want to check it out, on the cool Roppongi district. Had a NZ beer tapover, not so many local crafts. Serves food.
Good service and decent food to pair with your fresh, fresh, fresh Punk IPA. Pro-tip: The sampler is a good idea if you want to try all the single hop IPAs.
So many taps including Japanese local beers and great food are available. Staff are very kind and fluent Japanese/English speakers. Anyway, you must visit!
Do you really need a British rendition of an American brew pub serving odd food concoctions in the middle of Tokyo? Fish and chips only good choice in case you have to.
Good beers, and quite a classy modern place. Sadly only open till midnight so you end up getting turfed out and ending up in Hub across the road. Not too smokey!
Mushroom & Veg is the healthiest beer snack here. Even with the bacon on top
Music is quite British. Love the  atmosphere on Sunday night here, not too many people. I heardcore You. Recommend!
Various kinds of beer. The water is also on the tap in the restroom.
Hardcore IPA? Too hard core üòÖ(ask for a sample). Try instead the Punk IPA, very nice creation.
Get the tasting beer menu and you would find your favorite beer for sure!
